==English==
===Etymology===
: (weatherproofing) From original flashing material of [[copper]] or [[aluminum]] that [[reflect]]s flashes of [[sunlight]].

===Noun===
'''Flashing'''
# '''Flashing''' is the [[weatherproof]] [[shielding]] put around objects which [[protrude]] from the [[roof]] of a [[building]] (such as [[pipe]]s and [[chimney]]s, or the edges of other roofs) to deflect [[water]] away from the [[seam]]s.
# In [[retail]], '''flashing''' is getting rid of gaps on shelves, products are brought from the back of the shelf to the front to create a 'fuller' shelf.

===Adjective===
'''Flashing'''
# The [[blink]]ing of a [[light]] source, such as a [[light bulb]] or [[computer]]'s [[cursor (computers)|cursor]].

===Verb===
'''Flashing'''
# The process of writing to or updating flash memories such as the [[BIOS]] found on [[computer]] [[motherboard]]s or the rewritable cartridges used by developers of software for [[video game console]]s.
# A reference to [[indecent exposure]] (''i.e.'' to "flash" one's nude body in public at another unsuspecting person). The [[Mardi Gras]] festival is famous for flashing, which is often used to collect "throws" by attracting attention.

